definition.value: Neuron with an axon and two or more dendrites.
The right cerebral hemisphere is one of two bilateral, largely symmetrical organ subdivisions within the telencephalon which contain the cerebral cortex and cerebral white matter.
Protein that primarily constitutes an intermediate filament which provide strength or anchorage of other cellular structures. Examples: keratin, vimentin, desmin.
Cell component which consists of the plasma membrane and the cytoplasm surrounding the nucleus.
Cell component which consists of parts of the cytoplasm and plasma membrane protruding from the cell body. Examples: cilium, microvillus, axon.
Neuron with two neurites that are fused grossly when they protrude from the soma and bifurcate a short distance from the soma.
Cell appendage of a neuron that consists of an axon hillock, an axon proper,  axon collaterals and an axon terminal.
Cell appendage of a neuron that consists of the dendrite proper and the dendritic spines.

label.value: Zone of trunk of azygos vein

definition.value: Occipital lobe is the one of five lobes of the cerebral hemisphere which occupies the posterior-most portion of the hemisphere.  Anteriorly, it shares an arbitrary border with the parietal lobe and temporal lobe.  Medially, it is bounded by the longitudinal cerebral fissure.
Somatic cell which has as direct parts of its cytoplasm myofibrils organized in various patterns.
The insula is the one of five lobes of the cerebral hemisphere. It lies in the depths of  the lateral fissure and is covered by portions of the frontal, parietal and temporal lobes.
Definitive germ cell of the male sex.
